---
const problems = [
  {
    title: 'Spec drift',
    body: 'By the time a feature ships, the original intent has been filtered through interpretation, assumption, and urgency. The spec and the code no longer describe the same thing.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Philosophy–implementation gap',
    body: 'There is no mechanism for ensuring code satisfies the original "why." Features that pass QA can still betray the design intent that motivated them.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Unreliable AI output without validation',
    body: 'AI can generate code quickly. It cannot verify that code satisfies intent. Speed without validation doesn\'t reduce risk — it compounds it.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Documents nobody reads',
    body: 'Google Docs specs exist outside the development workflow. They\'re consulted rarely and abandoned freely. They are not the source of truth; they are a record of what was once intended.',
  },
];
---

<section
  data-test="problem-section"
  style="padding: 4rem 1.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);"
>
  <div style="max-width: 72rem; margin: 0 auto;">
    <h2 style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: clamp(1.375rem, 3vw, 2rem); font-weight: 400; color: var(--color-text-primary); margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
      Why existing approaches fail
    </h2>
    <p style="font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); margin-bottom: 3rem; max-width: 40rem;">
      The drift problem is not unique to any team or toolchain. It emerges from the structure of software development itself.
    </p>

    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(min(100%, 22rem), 1fr)); gap: 2rem;">
      {problems.map((p) => (
        <div style="border-left: 2px solid var(--color-border); padding-left: 1.25rem;">
          <h3 style="font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 0.9375rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text-primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
            {p.title}
          </h3>
          <p style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 0.9375rem; color: var(--color-text-secondary); line-height: 1.65;">
            {p.body}
          </p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
